[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13422] made 
``save``
 print to stderr when needed
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13486] created a security policy
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13529] fixed up an example
 and did tons of refactoring: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13525] replaced the manual 
``Record::get``
 implementation
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13524] lifted 
``SharedCow::to_mut``
 out of if let branches
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13522] simplified column look-up in 
``default``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13499] bumped rust toolchain
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13498] made contentious clippy fixes
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13497] fixed clippy issues for toolchain bump
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13455] fixed clippy issues from stable and nightly
Embers-of-the-Fire 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13526] fixed an overflowing table in command documentation
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13507] fixed an internal panic for 
``query web``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13505] added a new 
``--upgrade``
 flag for 
``mv``
 command
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13519] clarified 
``default``
 command help
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13513] added doc and examples for multi-dot directory traversal
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13511] clarified 
``random chars``
 documentation
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13503] clarified 
``random int``
 help
cablehead 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13181] made ctrlc available to plugins
IanManske kept working on migrating to Nu-specific path types: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13368] part 3: 
``$nu``
 paths
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13373] part 4: various tests
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13506] set content type metadata on all core 
``to *``
 commands
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13495] made pipeline metadata available to plugins
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13502] made a change to consider numbers to be part of a word in 
``split words``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13488] added links to security contacts
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13487] made 
``math sqrt``
 const
userwiths 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13442] made 
``log``
 respect 
``use_ansi_coloring``
 setting
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13485] bumped version to 
``0.96.2``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13471] fixed bad method links in docstrings
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13469] cleaned up arguments added to stack after 
``CallDecl``
 engine call
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13467] fixed incorrect capturing of subexpressions in IR
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13385] made assignment and 
``const``
 consistent with 
``let``
/
``mut``
maxim-uvarov 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13464] stopped forcing stripping of ANSI codes from strings in 
``stor``
Bahex 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13461] supplied 
``<acc>``
 to the closure as pipeline input in reduce
suimong 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13449] added "--as-columns" flag to 
``polars into-df``
qfel 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13409] used the Default implementation of Suggestion
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13406] factored out style-setting code
lyuha 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13321] kept forward slash when autocompleting on Windows
